<p dir="ltr"><span>An ECCE teacher observes that a child in his class has difficulty expressing herself orally and uses a limited vocabulary. Which of the following strategies would likely be most helpful in developing the child's expressive communication and vocabulary?</span></p>";s:18:"questiontextformat";s:1:"1";s:15:"generalfeedback";s:0:"";s:21:"generalfeedbackformat";s:1:"1";s:11:"defaultmark";d:1;s:7:"penalty";d:0.3333333;s:5:"qtype";s:11:"multichoice";s:6:"length";s:1:"1";s:5:"stamp";s:36:"eccetrainings.pk+211122231457+wSWANH";s:7:"version";s:36:"eccetrainings.pk+211201213815+GpAO7h";s:6:"hidden";s:1:"0";s:11:"timecreated";s:10:"1637622897";s:12:"timemodified";s:10:"1638394695";s:9:"createdby";s:1:"2";s:10:"modifiedby";s:1:"2";s:8:"idnumber";N;s:9:"contextid";s:2:"25";s:7:"options";O:8:"stdClass":15:{s:2:"id";s:2:"35";s:10:"questionid";s:2:"65";s:6:"layout";s:1:"0";s:6:"single";s:1:"1";s:14:"shuffleanswers";s:1:"1";s:15:"correctfeedback";s:23:"Your answer is correct.";s:21:"correctfeedbackformat";s:1:"1";s:24:"partiallycorrectfeedback";s:33:"Your answer is partially correct.";s:30:"partiallycorrectfeedbackformat";s:1:"1";s:17:"incorrectfeedback";s:25:"Your answer is incorrect.";s:23:"incorrectfeedbackformat";s:1:"1";s:15:"answernumbering";s:3:"abc";s:14:"shownumcorrect";s:1:"1";s:23:"showstandardinstruction";s:1:"0";s:7:"answers";a:4:{i:174;O:8:"stdClass":7:{s:2:"id";s:3:"174";s:8:"question";s:2:"65";s:6:"answer";s:141:"<p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"><span>encouraging the child to participate more while singing songs during circle time.</span><br></p>";s:12:"answerformat";s:1:"1";s:8:"fraction";s:9:"0.0000000";s:8:"feedback";s:0:"";s:14:"feedbackformat";s:1:"1";}i:175;O:8:"stdClass":7:{s:2:"id";s:3:"175";s:8:"question";s:2:"65";s:6:"answer";s:113:"<p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"><span>having the child listen to a variety of stories&nbsp;</span><br></p>";s:12:"answerformat";s:1:"1";s:8:"fraction";s:9:"0.0000000";s:8:"feedback";s:0:"";s:14:"fee